{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Separator · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Separator</h1>
    <p class="lead">A hairline that splits content into groups, horizontally or vertically.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Default</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.separator</code> to an <code>&lt;hr&gt;</code> for a full-width rule. The bare element stays untouched by reboot, so the class is the opt-in. Color tracks <code>--st-border</code> so it lands at the same weight as any other framed surface.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div>
      <p class="m-0">Backed up to iCloud just now.</p>
      <hr class="separator my-3">
      <p class="m-0">Local snapshot on this Mac. 2 days ago.</p>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Vertical</h2>
    <p>Drop the <code>--vertical</code> modifier on a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> inside a flex row. The rule stretches to the row's cross axis, so it sizes itself to whatever sits beside it. Add <code>role="separator"</code> and <code>aria-orientation="vertical"</code> when the divide carries meaning; skip the role attributes if it's purely decorative.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-row demo-row--gap-md text-muted-foreground fs-2">
      <span>By Maya Tanaka</span>
      <div class="separator separator--vertical" role="separator" aria-orientation="vertical"></div>
      <span>5 min read</span>
      <div class="separator separator--vertical" role="separator" aria-orientation="vertical"></div>
      <span>Tutorial</span>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Inside a card body</h2>
    <p>Use a separator to break a card into thematic blocks without piling on a header or footer. The rule reaches the body padding's edge, matching the cadence the rest of the card sets.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="card" style="max-width: 22rem;">
      <div class="card__body">
        <h5 class="card__title m-0">Invoice #2026-04-118</h5>
        <p class="card__subtitle m-0">Due July 1, 2026</p>
      </div>
      <hr class="separator">
      <div class="card__body">
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
          <span>Annual plan</span>
          <span class="fw-medium">$96.00</span>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
          <span>Three additional seats</span>
          <span class="fw-medium">$36.00</span>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground">Estimated tax</span>
          <span class="text-muted-foreground fw-medium">$8.40</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <hr class="separator">
      <div class="card__body">
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between fs-4 fw-semibold">
          <span>Total</span>
          <span>$140.40</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>Two variables retune <code>.separator</code> without touching component CSS. Override on the element, on a parent scope, or on <code>:root</code>. The cascade scopes the change.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Variable</th>
            <th>Default</th>
            <th>Use</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--separator-thickness</code></td>
            <td>1px</td>
            <td>Rule weight. Bump to 2px for a louder split between major sections.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--separator-color</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-border)</td>
            <td>Rule color. Track <code>--st-border</code> by default so the rule sits at the same weight as the rest of the framed surfaces.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
